[SN]TITLE[SN]
PSNI question three children over fire at Londonderry school

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The police have questioned three children over a fire at Holy Child School in Londonderry on Monday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two 10-year-old boys and an 11-year-old girl voluntarily attended Strand Road police station in the city on Wednesday
A police spokesperson said the children were interviewed and subsequently released pending a report to the youth diversion officer.
Damage to the school buildings was limited and it opened to pupils on Tuesday morning.
